## Typography System

### **Font Families**
```css
/* Primary: Clean, highly readable for UI and short content */
font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;

/* Secondary: Readable serif for long-form content */
font-family: 'Merriweather', Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;

/* Monospace: Code, data, and precise information */
font-family: 'SF Mono', Monaco, 'Cascadia Code', 'Roboto Mono', monospace;
```

### **Type Scale**
| Use Case | Size | Weight | Line Height | Letter Spacing |
|----------|------|--------|-------------|----------------|
| **Hero Headline** | 48px | 700 | 1.1 | -0.02em |
| **Page Title** | 32px | 600 | 1.2 | -0.01em |
| **Section Header** | 24px | 600 | 1.3 | 0 |
| **Subsection** | 20px | 500 | 1.4 | 0 |
| **Body Large** | 18px | 400 | 1.6 | 0 |
| **Body Default** | 16px | 400 | 1.6 | 0 |
| **Body Small** | 14px | 400 | 1.5 | 0 |
| **Caption** | 12px | 500 | 1.4 | 0.01em |

### **Typography Rules**
- **Maximum line length**: 75 characters for optimal readability
- **Paragraph spacing**: 1.5x the line height between paragraphs
- **Heading spacing**: 2x line height above, 0.5x below
- **Never use all caps** for body text (accessibility concern)
- **Limit font weights**: Regular (400), Medium (500), Semibold (600), Bold (700)

