## Data Visualization Guidelines

### **Dashboard Metrics**

#### **Large Number Display**
```css
.metric-primary {
  font-size: 64px;
  font-weight: 300; /* Light weight for large numbers */
  line-height: 1;
  color: var(--color-text);
}

.metric-label {
  font-size: 18px;
  font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  margin-top: 8px;
}

.metric-secondary {
  font-size: 14px;
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
  margin-top: 4px;
}
```

#### **Data Visualization Principles**
1. **Direct labeling** over legends when possible
2. **Consistent color coding** across all charts
3. **Accessible color palettes** (colorblind-friendly)
4. **Clear units and scales** for all numerical data
5. **Progressive disclosure** for complex datasets

