## Interactive States

### **Standard State Definitions**

#### **Interactive Element States**
```css
/* Default State */
.interactive {
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
}

/* Hover State */
.interactive:hover {
  transform: translateY(-1px);
  color: var(--color-primary);
}

/* Focus State (keyboard navigation) */
.interactive:focus {
  outline: 2px solid var(--color-primary);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

/* Active State */
.interactive:active {
  transform: translateY(0);
}

/* Disabled State */
.interactive:disabled {
  opacity: 0.6;
  cursor: not-allowed;
  transform: none;
}
```

#### **Loading States**
- **Skeleton screens** for content loading
- **Subtle animations** (avoid overwhelming motion)
- **Clear progress indicators** for longer operations
- **Maintain layout** during loading (prevent layout shift)

